{
  "genre": "hiphop",
  "mode": "energize",
  "mixStrategy": "FREQUENCY SEPARATION: Bass (Synth Bass 38) owns 20-300Hz with sub notes D1-D2 (MIDI 26-38), providing the 808-style foundation. Chords (Warm Pad 89) fill 300Hz-2kHz with dark minor voicings in C3-C5 (MIDI 48-72). Melody (Vibraphone 11) cuts through at 1-8kHz in C4-C6 (MIDI 60-79). Drums span full spectrum rhythmically with boom-bap kick/snare locking to bass hits.\n\nHARMONIC UNITY: All tracks follow i (Dm) \u2192 iv (Gm) \u2192 bVI (Bb) \u2192 bVII (C) progression in 4-bar phrases (~8.35s per phrase). Bass plays roots D, G, Bb, C. Chords voice full minor/major triads. Melody targets chord tones on beats 1 and 3 with pentatonic passing tones on weak beats.\n\nRHYTHMIC INTERLOCK: Kick and bass lock together on beat 1 and beat 3. Snare cracks on 2 and 4. Hi-hats run 16th-note patterns with velocity accents creating groove. Melody phrases sit slightly behind the beat with syncopated rhythms that breathe between snare hits. Bass sustains long under everything.\n\nENERGY ARC (6 segments ~7.5s each): Seg1 (0-7.5s) 0.4 \u2014 sparse intro, just kick/hat + bass + light pad. Seg2 (7.5-15s) 0.6 \u2014 snare enters, melody begins simple motif. Seg3 (15-22.5s) 0.8 \u2014 full groove, melody becomes more active, hats get denser. Seg4 (22.5-30s) 0.9 \u2014 peak energy building, velocity increases, drum fills. Seg5 (30-37.5s) 1.0 \u2014 full blast, all elements at max density and velocity. Seg6 (37.5-45s) 0.7 \u2014 pull back, melody thins out, energy winds down but groove continues.",
